column3: 45 min HIIT & Hills Ride with Robin Arzon
column5: 45 min HIIT & Hills Ride from 4/1/20. Taken by jt_speedfreak on Peloton.

Every run, if a car moves over I give a wave. If the car hugs the center line, maybe a slight nod. If it doesn't move at all, I'll give a wave of my arm to get the attention and hopefully they move over.

Today some angry-with-the-world that only knows the words "me" "I" and "mine" got a arm wave when he didn't move over on an empty upper Snowden. A couple minutes later, he pulls up next to me from behind and stops, yelling about the white line and that he's tired of runners owning the roads and how he pays taxes.

What the hell is wrong with people?! Go talk to a therapist and figure out why you weren't hugged enough as a kid and how hopefully your taxes pay for a better education than what you got.
